Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel!). Pop the wedges on a large #baking tray{} in a single layer. Drizzle with @oil{}, then season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out and roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 2cm sized chunks. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30}(grated). Zest the @lime{1} and cut into wedges. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(grated). Drain and rinse the @black beans{1%400g can} in a #colander{} then pop in a #bowl{}. Using the back of a #fork{} lightly crush the beans. Drain and rinse the @sweetcorn{150}.

Place a #cereal bowl{} upside down on your #chopping board{}. Prick your @super soft tortillas with whole wheat{4} all over with a fork. Shape one of your tortillas around the outside of the bowl (to make your taco bowl shape!). Use a sheet of #foil{} to mould round the tortilla (and also take the shape of the bowl), press firmly down around the shape of the bowl folding up the excess foil around the outside of the bowl. Lift the foil wrapped tortilla off of the bowl and place right side up on a baking tray. Repeat for the other tortillas (2 per person). Bake in your oven until browned and crispy, ~{6-8%minutes}. Once cooked, remove from the oven and set aside.

Meanwhile, heat a splash of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on a medium high heat. When hot, add the @diced chicken thigh{260} and cook until browned all over, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add the @red pepper{1}(halved, core and seeds removed, chopped) and onion and cook until tender and starting to colour, another ~{4-5%minutes}. Add the garlic and @Mexican style spice mix{1%tsp} and cook stirring frequently for ~{1%minute}. Add the @tomato passata{1}, crushed beans, @chicken stock powder{1} and @water{100}(ml). Simmer until reduced to a thick sauce, ~{3-5%minutes}. IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle. Once cooked, taste and season with salt and pepper.

Whilst the filling cooks, slice lengthways into the @avocado{1}. Once you reach the stone turn the avocado around to cut it in half. Twist each half and pull it apart. Remove the stone then scoop out the flesh onto a #board{} and cut into 2cm chunks. Mix the @olive oil{for the salsa}, zest and a squeeze of lime juice, season with salt and pepper. Add the avocado and sweetcorn to the dressing and stir to coat.

Place 2 taco bowls on each plate and fill with the chicken fajita mix. Sprinkle over the grated cheddar followed by the avocado corn salsa. Crumble the @feta cheese{100} over, sprinkle the @?chilli flakes{1}(or less if you don't like too much heat) and a lime wedge to squeeze over. Serve the wedges on the side and enjoy!